Wash and dry all produce. Adjust oven rack to upper position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Mince or grate @garlic{1/2%tsp} until you have ½ tsp (you'll have a clove left over). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Cut @broccoli florets{16%oz} into florets.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} and as much of the garlic as you like (start with a pinch and go up from there). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{2%tbsp} and @sugar{2%tsp}. Continue cooking until syrupy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from pan and set aside in another small bowl. Wash out pan.

While onion cooks, toss together broccoli and 1 TBSP aioli in a #medium bowl{} until florets are evenly coated. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @dried oregano{2%tsp}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper and toss so that crumbs stick to broccoli.

> TIP: It's OK if not all the breadcrumbs stick.

Spread broccoli out on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake in oven, tossing halfway through, until panko is golden brown, about ~{15%minutes}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Shape @ground beef{20%oz} into four patties (make them slightly wider than the buns). Season with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook until patties almost reach desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Sprinkle patties evenly with @Monterey Jack cheese{1%cup}. Cover pan and continue cooking until cheese melts, about ~{1%minute}.

While patties cook, split @potato buns{4} in half and place on another baking sheet. Toast in oven until golden, about ~{3%minutes}. Spread @ketchup{4%tbsp} and remaining aioli onto buns. Fill each with a beef patty and as much onion jam as you like. Serve with broccoli on the side.